Just a note on the previous reviewer. 6 Brioche is right because when you cut them into 3 slices each, you get 18 slices, which is 2 more than 2 each. I guess you get to munch on those while you poach the eggs!

Rating: 3
We loved this recipe, a variation on eggs benedict but less rich. However, I think there are some errors in the recipe. It calls for 6 individual brioches, but the recipe serves 8 people.I used slices of challah bread instead because I couldn't get brioches in my small town. I thought using a tomato slice instead of avocado whould cut down on the richness and provide a contrasting texture. The directions also say to preheat the oven to 350 degrees. What for? Do use the sorrel or arugula as this provides a nice contrast to the smooth eggs and salmon. I don't think it takes a whole hour to prepare. This makes a wonderful celebration brunch dish.